            "date": "2024",
            "title": "Modelling and assessing long-term urban transportation system resilience based on system dynamics",
            "authors": "Nanxi Wang; Min Wu; Kum Fai Yuen",
            "keywords": "urban transportation systems; long-term resilience; system dynamics; climate change; sustainability",
            "abstract": "Urban transportation systems (UTSs) face numerous long-term disturbances, such as climate change, technological innovation, and pandemics, highlighting the need for resilient construction and management. However, current research on this area remains insufficient. Consequently, this paper aims to establish a model for evaluating the long-term resilience of UTSs and identify strategic enhancement methods through simulation. Given the intricate interdependencies among diverse components within UTSs, a dynamic system model tailored for the long-term resilience assessment of UTSs is formulated. Leveraging the developed model and data from Singapore's UTS, evolutionary analysis, local sensitivity analysis, global sensitivity analysis using the Monte Carlo simulation, and strategy analysis were conducted to reveal the evolutionary law of long-term resilience and put forward targeted resilience promotion strategies, providing a theoretical basis and practical guidance for the sustainable development of urban transportation systems.",
            "citation": "Wang, Nanxi, Wu, Min, & Yuen, Kum Fai. (2024). Modelling and assessing long-term urban transportation system resilience based on system dynamics. Sustainable Cities and Society, 109, Article 105548. https://doi.org/10.1016/j.scs.2024.105548",
