            "status": "Published",
            "articleType": "Journal Article",
            "journalShort": "Transp. Res. Part D",
            "journalFull": "Transportation Research Part D: Transport and Environment",
            "date": "2024",
            "title": "Urban transportation system long-term resilience assessment using multi-dimensional dynamic Bayesian network",
            "authors": "Nanxi Wang; Min Wu; Kum Fai Yuen; Xueyi Gao",
            "keywords": "urban transportation systems; long-term resilience; dynamic Bayesian network; multidimensional assessment; uncertainty",
            "abstract": "Urban transportation systems are vulnerable to long-term uncertainties such as climate change, population growth, and technological updates, which pose challenges to the stable operation of the systems. To accurately assess the long-term resilience of urban transportation systems under dynamic disturbances, this study constructs a multi-dimensional dynamic Bayesian network model. The model integrates economic, social, environmental, and technical dimensions, realizes the dynamic tracking of resilience changes over time, and quantifies the uncertainty of resilience assessment. Taking Singapore's urban transportation system as an example, the effectiveness of the model is verified. The results show that the model can accurately predict the long-term resilience evolution trend, identify key vulnerability factors, and provide decision support for formulating phased resilience enhancement strategies.",
