            "journalFull": "Journal of Retailing and Consumer Services",
            "date": "2024",
            "title": "An investigation of consumer switching intention on the use of automated courier station from a signaling perspective",
            "authors": "Zhaotong Li; Min Wu; Chee-Chong Teo; Kum Fai Yuen",
            "keywords": "automated courier station; switching intention; signaling theory; perceived green value; last-mile delivery",
            "abstract": "With the rapid development of intelligent logistics, automated courier stations have gradually become an important part of the last-mile delivery service. However, consumers' switching intention to use automated courier stations is affected by many factors. Based on the signaling theory, this study explores the determinants of consumers' switching intention to automated courier stations. Through a questionnaire survey of 480 consumers and structural equation model analysis, it is found that functional signals (convenience, efficiency), emotional signals (trust, satisfaction), and environmental signals (policy support, technical reliability) all have significant positive impacts on consumers' switching intention. In addition, perceived value plays a mediating role in the relationship between signals and switching intention. This study enriches the application of signaling theory in the field of intelligent logistics and provides practical suggestions for the promotion and operation of automated courier stations.",
            "citation": "Li, Zhaotong, Wu, Min, Teo, Chee-Chong, & Yuen, Kum Fai. (2024). An investigation of consumer switching intention on the use of automated courier station from a signaling perspective. Journal of Retailing and Consumer Services, 78, Article 103768. https://doi.org/10.1016/j.jretconser.2024.103768",
            "notes": "Volume 78, Article 103768. DOI: https://doi.org/10.1016/j.jretconser.2024.103768. CV notes: IF 13.1; CAS Management Q1 Top; JCR Business Q1. Bibliographic metadata from uploaded CV; abstract from PAPERS.txt."
