            "journalShort": "Sci. Total Environ.",
            "journalFull": "Science of the Total Environment",
            "date": "2024",
            "title": "Investigating the determinants of Singaporean citizens' attitudes toward marine litter pollution control: A policy acceptance model",
            "authors": "Liren Chen; Qingji Zhou; Min Wu; Kum Fai Yuen; Renliang Huang; Rongxin Su",
            "keywords": "marine litter; pollution control; policy acceptance; Singapore; environmental governance",
            "abstract": "Marine litter pollution has become a global environmental problem, and public attitude and policy acceptance are crucial to the effectiveness of pollution control. This study constructs a policy acceptance model based on the theory of planned behavior and environmental concern theory to explore the determinants of Singaporean citizens' attitudes toward marine litter pollution control. A total of 520 valid questionnaires were collected, and the data were analyzed using partial least squares structural equation modeling. The results show that environmental concern, perceived behavioral control, subjective norms, and policy awareness all significantly positively affect citizens' attitudes toward marine litter pollution control policies. The research results provide a theoretical basis for the formulation and implementation of marine litter pollution control policies in Singapore and other countries.",
            "citation": "Chen, Liren, Zhou, Qingji, Wu, Min, Yuen, Kum Fai, Huang, Renliang, & Su, Rongxin. (2024). Investigating the determinants of Singaporean citizens' attitudes toward marine litter pollution control: A policy acceptance model. Science of the Total Environment, 957, Article 177566. https://doi.org/10.1016/j.scitotenv.2024.177566",
            "notes": "Volume 957, Article 177566. DOI: https://doi.org/10.1016/j.scitotenv.2024.177566. CV notes: IF 8.0; CAS Environmental Sciences & Ecology Q2 Top; JCR Environmental Sciences Q1. Bibliographic metadata from uploaded CV; abstract from PAPERS.txt."
