            "status": "Published",
            "articleType": "Journal Article",
            "journalShort": "J. Environ. Manag.",
            "journalFull": "Journal of Environmental Management",
            "date": "2023",
            "title": "Willingness to participate in virtual reality technologies: Public adoption and policy perspectives for marine conservation",
            "authors": "Le Yi Koh; Min Wu; Xueqin Wang; Kum Fai Yuen",
            "keywords": "virtual reality; marine conservation; public adoption; policy perspectives; environmental education",
            "abstract": "Virtual reality (VR) technology provides a new way for marine conservation publicity and education, but the public's willingness to participate in VR-based marine conservation activities is affected by many factors. This study combines the technology acceptance model and environmental psychology theory to explore the determinants of the public's willingness to participate in VR marine conservation technologies. A survey of 460 Singaporean residents was conducted, and structural equation modeling was used for data analysis. The results show that perceived usefulness, perceived ease of use, environmental concern, and subjective norms significantly positively affect the public's willingness to participate, while perceived cost has a significant negative impact. The research results provide policy suggestions for promoting VR technology in marine conservation and improving public participation.",
            "citation": "Koh, Le Yi, Wu, Min, Wang, Xueqin, & Yuen, Kum Fai. (2023). Willingness to participate in virtual reality technologies: Public adoption and policy perspectives for marine conservation. Journal of Environmental Management, 334, Article 117480. https://doi.org/10.1016/j.jenvman.2023.117480",
            "notes": "Volume 334, Article 117480. DOI: https://doi.org/10.1016/j.jenvman.2023.117480. CV notes: IF 8.4; CAS Environmental Sciences & Ecology Q2 Top; JCR Environmental Sciences Q1. Bibliographic metadata from uploaded CV; abstract from PAPERS.txt."
