            "articleType": "Journal Article",
            "journalShort": "Transp. Res. Part A",
            "journalFull": "Transportation Research Part A: Policy and Practice",
            "date": "2023",
            "title": "Initial trust formation on shared autonomous vehicles: Exploring the effects of personality-, transfer- and performance-based stimuli",
            "authors": "Min Wu; Kum Fai Yuen",
            "keywords": "initial trust; shared autonomous vehicles; personality-based stimuli; trust transfer; performance-based stimuli",
            "abstract": "Initial trust is the key to users' acceptance and use of shared autonomous vehicles (SAVs) in the early stage of promotion. Based on the trust formation theory, this study explores the effects of three types of stimuli (personality-based stimuli, transfer-based stimuli, performance-based stimuli) on the initial trust formation of SAVs. A 3×2 between-subjects experiment was conducted with 420 participants, and the results show that all three types of stimuli can significantly promote the formation of initial trust, among which performance-based stimuli have the strongest effect. In addition, perceived risk plays a moderating role in the relationship between stimuli and initial trust. This study enriches the theory of trust formation in autonomous systems and provides a basis for the early promotion and user trust cultivation of SAVs.",
            "citation": "Wu, Min, & Yuen, Kum Fai. (2023). Initial trust formation on shared autonomous vehicles: Exploring the effects of personality-, transfer- and performance-based stimuli. Transportation Research Part A: Policy and Practice, 173, Article 103704. https://doi.org/10.1016/j.tra.2023.103704",
            "notes": "Volume 173, Article 103704. DOI: https://doi.org/10.1016/j.tra.2023.103704. CV notes: IF 6.8; CAS Engineering Q1 Top; JCR Economics Q1. Bibliographic metadata from uploaded CV; abstract from PAPERS.txt."
