            "journalShort": "J. Clean. Prod.",
            "journalFull": "Journal of Cleaner Production",
            "date": "2023",
            "title": "A theoretical model for preventing marine litter behaviour: An empirical evidence from Singapore",
            "authors": "Liren Chen; Qingji Zhou; Lingjie Yue; Min Wu; Renliang Huang; Kum Fai Yuen; Rongxin Su",
            "keywords": "marine litter; prevention behaviour; Singapore; environmental behaviour; planned behaviour",
            "abstract": "Marine litter behavior is the main cause of marine litter pollution, and it is urgent to construct an effective prevention model. Based on the theory of planned behavior and norm activation model, this study constructs a theoretical model for preventing marine litter behavior, and verifies it with empirical data from Singapore. A total of 500 valid questionnaires were collected, and the data were analyzed using partial least squares structural equation modeling. The results show that personal norms, perceived behavioral control, and environmental awareness significantly negatively affect marine litter behavior, while subjective norms have an indirect impact through personal norms. The model has good explanatory power and can provide a theoretical basis for formulating targeted marine litter prevention strategies.",
            "citation": "Chen, Liren, Zhou, Qingji, Yue, Lingjie, Wu, Min, Huang, Renliang, Yuen, Kum Fai, & Su, Rongxin. (2023). A theoretical model for preventing marine litter behaviour: An empirical evidence from Singapore. Journal of Cleaner Production, 427, Article 139109. https://doi.org/10.1016/j.jclepro.2023.139109",
            "notes": "Volume 427, Article 139109. DOI: https://doi.org/10.1016/j.jclepro.2023.139109. CV notes: IF 10.0; CAS Environmental Sciences & Ecology Q1 Top; JCR Environmental Sciences Q1. Bibliographic metadata from uploaded CV; abstract from PAPERS.txt."
