            "status": "Published",
            "articleType": "Journal Article",
            "journalShort": "Transp. Res. Part D",
            "journalFull": "Transportation Research Part D: Transport and Environment",
            "date": "2020",
            "title": "Determinants of ship operators’ options for compliance with IMO 2020",
            "authors": "Kevin X. Li; Min Wu; Xiaohan Gu; Kum Fai Yuen; Yi Xiao",
            "keywords": "IMO 2020; ship operators; compliance options; low-sulphur fuel; scrubbers; LNG",
            "abstract": "The International Maritime Organization (IMO) 2020 regulation, which limits the sulphur content in marine fuels to 0.5% globally, has forced ship operators to choose among various compliance options, including using low-sulphur fuel oil, installing scrubbers, or switching to alternative fuels like liquefied natural gas (LNG). This study aims to identify the key determinants influencing ship operators’ compliance decisions. Using institutional theory and the resource-based view, the study develops a conceptual framework and tests it using survey data from 210 ship operators worldwide. The results reveal that regulatory pressure, cost considerations, technical feasibility, and firm size significantly affect the choice of compliance strategy. Additionally, environmental awareness and long-term strategic planning moderate the relationship between these factors and compliance decisions. The findings provide valuable insights for policymakers, industry stakeholders, and ship operators to understand the drivers of compliance behavior and develop supportive policies for the transition to cleaner marine fuels.",
            "citation": "Li, Kevin X., Wu, Min, Gu, Xiaohan, Yuen, Kum Fai, & Xiao, Yi. (2020). Determinants of ship operators’ options for compliance with IMO 2020. Transportation Research Part D: Transport and Environment, 86, Article 102459. https://doi.org/10.1016/j.trd.2020.102459",
